emuInput.TitMainTitle: Thelma Bennett wearing light colored quilted satin robe with collar, seated on bed holding newborn son Freddie, with nurse on right, in interior with light colored walls
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 22, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "16th Child - Mrs. Thelma Bennett of 12 Monhagen St., North Side, fondly holds her newborn son. The baby, named Freddie, is the only one of Mrs. Bennett's children born by Caesarean section.  Mother and child are "doing well," - Harris Photo."
